@HuskyCass Absolutely! And not living in survival mode. A lot of times poor people can’t do the “wealthy habit” things bc they have no time from working so much and/or managing the difficulties of living life w/o enough money.

I think poor & wealthy people have a lot in common. The middle class is where most horrible habits lie. That’s where ppl make *enough* but spend too much, don’t prioritize health, etc. Poor & wealthy folks are usually both working hard &/or smart. Just diff stages of the game.

Poor people often just need guidance reframing how to use their money to build a solid base for their families now that they’re out of survival mode. Survival mode does ugly things to your brain & having enough can be hard to navigate.

For my Junior League assignment, I’m a budget mentor for ppl in a program who are working to get living wage jobs w/benefits & establish financial security for their families. Usually but not always single moms. They gave us this advice: Don’t patronize them. They know ab money.
Poor people are often better with money than non-poor people. They have to stretch dollars in ways we who make enough money can’t imagine. The Rich Habits vs Poor Habits is a false dichotomy.
